  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed mansard roof extension, due to its excessive design, scale, siting, height and bulk and visual prominence would form a dominant and discordant addition to the property being readily visible from the public and private realm. The addition would detrimentally compete with the neighbouring Grade II listed buildings and as a result fail to retain the host building's current subordinate scale. The proposal is inappropriate as it harms the setting of the neighbouring Grade II listed buildings and fails to preserve the character and appearance of the St Mary Magdalene Conservation Area. The proposal is contrary to the NPPF 2019, policies 7.4, 7.6 and 7.8 of the London Plan 2016, policy CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011, policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of Islington's Development Management Policies 2013, and the guidance contained within Islington's Urban Design Guide and the Conservation Area Design Guidelines."
